 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Protection Paladin Phase 2 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 293 top-ranked Protection Paladin DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 2 (Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Protection Paladin items in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Crystalforge Legguards (86%), Crystalforge Handguards (85%), Justicar Chestguard (83%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Serpentshrine Cavern and Tempest Keep."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Protection Paladin use in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "Powerful Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Solid Star of Elune and Glowing Nightseye in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Protection Paladin need in Phase 2?",
   "answer": "11 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of the Defender on head, Greater Inscription of the Knight on shoulders, Nethercleft Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Major Spellpower on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of the Defender comes from Alurmi — Caverns of Time."
  }
 ]
